        <name>1.4.2.8 Divide fractions 1</name>
        <questiontext>&lt;p class="HELM_exercise"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Leave the expression in its most simplified form&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;\( \dfrac{\displaystyle {@n1@}}{@exp1@} =\) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]&lt;/p&gt;</questiontext>
        <questiontextformat>1</questiontextformat>
        <generalfeedback>&lt;p&gt;We can write the fraction as:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;\(\dfrac{\displaystyle {@n1@}}{@exp1@} = \displaystyle {@n1@} \div \dfrac{@exp1@}{@1@}\)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Inverting the second fraction and multiplying we find:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;\(\displaystyle {@n1@} \times \dfrac{1}{@exp1@} = {@ta1@}\)&lt;/p&gt;</generalfeedback>
